subject: Switched bmcweb to use new telemetry service API
commitMessage:
Switched bmcweb to use new telemetry service API

Added support for multiple MetricProperties. Added support for new
parameters: CollectionTimeScope, CollectionDuration.

Tested:
  - It is possible to create MetricReportDefinitions with multiple
    MetricProperties.
  - Stub values for new parameters are correctly passed to telemetry
    service.
  - All existing telemetry service functionalities remain unchanged.

Change-Id: I2cd17069e3ea015c8f5571c29278f1d50536272a
Signed-off-by: Krzysztof Grobelny <krzysztof.grobelny@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Lukasz Kazmierczak <lukasz.kazmierczak@intel.com>

Please don't use exceptions for control flow in bmcweb.  This is documented in DEVELOPING.md, and prevents optimizations that decrease our binary size.

Please use the more common looping mechanism until unpackProperties is better understood in a bmcweb context.  If this is a pattern you want to see happen, please update some of the existing code to use it, and we can evaluate it outside the context of new code.
FYI, CI failure was likely a false positive.  We had a breaking change in boost URI, and this got caught in the crossfire.  I rebased it, and the rebase should give a better result.
